column24: rationale
Cadherin-1, integrity of epithelial cell adhesion, membrane protein and can be used for segmentation of most epithelial cells in lung
Collagen alpha-1(I) chain, extracellular matrix protein prominent in the lung adventitia
Proliferation marker protein
Actin alpha-2, alpha smooth muscle actin, a protein essential for structure and function of smooth muscle cells
Pulmonary surfactant-associated protein C unique to type II alveolar epithelial cells
T-cell surface glycoprotein
Macrosialin, transmembrane glycoprotein that serves as a marker for macrophages and monocytes
Receptor-type tyrosine-protein phosphatase C expressed in variable intensities on all leukocytes
T-cell surface glycoprotein, CD1c positive myeloid DC
T-cell surface glycoprotein CD3 epsilon chain
B-lymphocyte antigen
Platelet endothelial cell adhesion molecule, vascular endothelial cells

Platelet factor 4, a small protein released by platelets that helps blood clot and alerts the immune system. It's also known as chemokine ligand 4 (CXCL4), used to identify megakaryocytes and platelets in lung
Lymphatic vessel endothelial hyaluronic acid receptor 1

column3: HGNC:6412, HGNC:6439, HGNC:6440, HGNC:6441, HGNC:6442, HGNC:6443, HGNC:6444, HGNC:20406, HGNC:6445, HGNC:6446, HGNC:6413, HGNC:6416, HGNC:6421, HGNC:6423, HGNC:6436

column24: Majority if not all lung epithelium
T-cell surface glycoprotein CD8 alpha chain
HLA class II histocompatibility antigen, DR alpha chain, antigen presenting cells
Advanced glycosylation end product-specific receptor, type I epithelial alveolar
Tumor protein 63, basal cells airway epithileum
Tryptase alpha/beta-1, neutral peptidase found in most mast cells
Monocyte differentiation antigen CD14, macrophage marker
Sodium/potassium-transporting ATPase subunit beta-3, membrane segmentation
Scavenger receptor cysteine-rich type 1 protein M130, non-inflammatory macrophages, monocyte-derived macrophages
Collagen alpha-1(IV) chain,  extracellular matrix, produced primarily by fibroblasts, endothelial cells and smooth muscle cells
Keratin, type II cytoskeletal 5, basal cells of airway epithelium
Forkhead box protein P3, regulatory T cells
Integrin alpha-X; dendritic cells/macrophages
Myeloperoxidase, enzyme found primarily in the azurophilic granules of neutrophils, also in macrophage to lesser extent
Sciellin; some type I alveolar epithelial cell; involved in cell cornification and survival
Neuron-specific beta-III-tubulin, expressed in all neurons
Uteroglobin, small, cysteine-rich protein also known as club cell secretory protein (CCSP) that is secreted into the extracellular space by club/airway secretory cells
Secretoglobin family 3A member 2 present in distal club-like airway cells; also found in some submucosal gland mucus cells
Apomucin major airway glycoprotein, goblet cell
Lymphatic endothelium

Keratin, type I cytoskeletal 14, co-exists in some basal cells wtih KRT5-KRT14 filaments to self-organize into large bundles and enhance mechanical properties; prominent in healthy mypoepithelial cells of submucosal glands

Transcription factor master regulator of ciliogenesis, the process of generating cilia. It controls the expression of genes essential for cilia structure and function. prominent in nuclei of multi-ciliated cells of lung airway
Gastrin-releasing peptide; pro-epithelial cell growth and proinflammatory; exclusive to neuroendocrine cell in lung
Pulmonary surfactant-associated protein B, type II alveolar epithelial cell, also subset of airway secretory (club cells) and airway basal cells
Complement decay acceleratiing factor; primarily type I pneumocytes (AT1) in lung

Podoplanin; a transmembrane glycoprotein expressed on the surface of lymphatic endothelial cells, mediates effects on cell migration and adhesion through its different partners; lymphatic endothelium; in lung also alveolar epithelium, type 1

Scaffolding protein within caveolar membranes; increased expression with cell stress;  facilitates identification of type I pneumocytes cells lacking AGER; also expressed in vascular endothelial cells and smc
Gel-forming mucin glycoprotein; contributes to lubricating and viscoelastic properties of mucus and saliva; mucus cells; subset of goblet cells
Transcription factor that regulates lung progenitor cell fate and plasticity during lung development, homeostasis and regenerative responses to lung injury; proximal airway epithelium
Transcription factor that regulates proliferative capacity and differentiation of lung epithelium; club cells; ciliated cells
Keratin, type II cytoskeletal 8; Expression is associated with transitional states of alveolar epithelial cells in injury and repair
